ng.Integer` or `java.lang.Long` values:\\n\\n```scala\\nHelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCall(x, x, \\\"sum\\\", args)\\n```\\n\\nThat then calls:\\n\\n```scala\\nhelperObj.getClass().getMethod(name, argsTypes: _*)\\nmethod.invoke(helperObj, nArgs: _*)\\n```\\n\\nHowever, `argsTypes` are derived via `arg.getClass`, so for `Int + Int` the lookup becomes:\\n\\n```java\\nInteger.class.getMethod(\\\"sum\\\", Integer.class, Integer.class)\\n```\\n\\nThe JDK exposes `Integer.sum(int, int)`, not `Integer.sum(Integer, Integer)`, so the lookup cannot succeed through the normal public jsoniter-scala macro API. Consequently, the later `Method#invoke` call site is not reachable through supported behavior in this artifact.\\n\\nCovering it would require either:\\n\\n- asserting this broken numeric compile-time-evaluation path,\\n- directly instantiating private/internal macro helper classes,\\n- using direct reflection against internals, or\\n- shadowing/modifying JDK/library classes,\\n\\nall of which violate the task rules.\\n\\nI also did not run tests, per instruction.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0c2f353477ff5f86016a1157b26944819f8b2af2527df09158\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 9328, \"output\": 1756, \"cacheRead\": 25600, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 36684, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1779521435407, \"responseId\": \"resp_0c2f353477ff5f86016a11579bfe2c819f80b1b3299bc61edd\"}}\n../4985-410317bd/human-intervention-logs/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala:jsoniter-scala-macros_3:2.33.3/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-23T07-31-01-114289Z.log:1634:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Clarifying method calls**\\n\\nI'm realizi